<P>And you, niece, I a&s;&s;ure you, have a very pro|per proportion (as undoubtedly your merit claims) of my un|feigned e&s;teem and good wi&s;hes; as likeways hath my worthy nephew, Sir Harry; whom I &s;hould have been proud to have found in this good company, and deem both my&s;elf and him unfortunate in his being ab&s;ent from it.</P>
