<DIV1 TYPE="epilogue">
<PB REF="940">
<HEAD>EPILOGUE.</HEAD>
<L>WHAT &s;trange odd maggots fill an author's pate?</L>
<L>A female court of ju&s;tice&mdash;rare conceit!</L>
<L>Ladies, I give you joy of your new &s;tations,</L>
<L>I think you've <HI>had</HI> a trial&mdash;of your patience.</L>
<L>What, five long acts, and not one plea&s;ant &s;ally!</L>
<L>But grave Sir Anthony's attempt to rally&mdash;</L>
<L>No &s;prightly rendezvous, no pretty fellows,</L>
<L>No wife intriguing, nor no husband jealous!</L>
<L>If to &s;uch innovations you &s;ubmit,</L>
<L>And &s;wallow tame morality for wit:</L>
<L>If &s;uch dull rules you let a woman teach,</L>
<L>Her next attempt, perhaps, will be to&mdash;preach.</L>
<L>I told her (for it vexed me to the heart).</L>
<L>Madam&mdash;excu&s;e me&mdash;I don't like my part&mdash;</L>
<L>'Tis out of nature&mdash;never drawn from life,</L>
<L>Who ever heard of &s;uch a pa&s;&s;ive wife?</L>
<L>To bear &s;o much&mdash;'tis not in fle&s;h and blood&mdash;</L>
<L>Such females might have liv'd before the flood.</L>
<L>But now the character will &s;eem &s;o flat,</L>
<L>Give <HI>me</HI> threats, tears, hy&s;terics, and all that&mdash;</L>
<L>If this dont work upon my Lord, I hope</L>
<L>You'll &s;o contrive the plot&mdash;I may elope.</L>
<L>Take my advice, I think I know the town,</L>
<L>Without &s;uch aids your piece will &s;carce go down.</L>
<L>Hold, friend, &s;he cry'd&mdash;I think I've hit the way</L>
<L>To reconcile both &s;exes to the play;</L>
<L>For, while the prologue bids our own be &s;ov'reign,</L>
<L>The &s;cenes in&s;truct the other how to govern.</L>
<L>A harmle&s;s plot&mdash;with credit to di&s;mi&s;s</L>
<L>The piece&mdash;you know the Ladies never hi&s;s.</L>
<L>And tho' they &s;hould condemn it, yet the men &s;ure</L>
<L>Will leave a woman's faults to women's cen&s;ure.</L>
<L>They, prone to meekne&s;s, charity, and love,</L>
<L>Are always &s;ilent where they can't approve.</L>
<L>But if to loud applau&s;e we dare to aim,</L>
<L>It is the men mu&s;t ratify our claim.</L>
<TRAILER>FINIS.</TRAILER>
</DIV1>
